<p>GDP growth: 1.4% GDP: $521bn (PPP: $439bn) Inflation: 2.6% Population: 10.7m GDP per head: $48,890 (PPP: $41,260)</p>

<p>Like a marriage with kids, the difficulties of separation may be the only thing keeping Belgium's Flemish-speakers and Francophones together. If agreement on a new government cannot be reached—and none has emerged since elections in June 2010—big issues, such as dealing with Europe's third-largest foreign debt burden, will also remain unresolved. The economy will stutter and the fiscal deficit will close just a bit.</p>

